name: pillowfort

name: eponymous
description: Non-token cards with a name matching their subtypes.

description: Cards with an additional cost of mana beyond the card's own colors.

name: repeated-keyword
description: Repetition or stacking of a keyword.

name: catch-up
description: Players who have less get more.

name: multi-character-card
description: This card represents multiple distinct identifiable characters on one face. Avoid using this for nameless mobs.

name: affinity
description: Affinity is an ability that reduces the mana cost of the spell by the number of permanents of a specified type that the player controls. Variations of this ability exist, such as referencing the number of cards in the players' graveyard or the number of attacking creatures.

name: affinity
description: Affinity is an ability that reduces the mana cost of the spell by the number of permanents of a specified type that the player controls. Variations of this ability exist, such as referencing the number of cards in the players' graveyard or the number of attacking creatures.

name: flicker-slow
description: Exile a card now, get it back later (usually end of turn).

name: alternate-cost-tap-creature
description: Cards that let you tap creatures to pay less or no mana for them.

name: alternate-cost-tap-creature
description: Cards that let you tap creatures to pay less or no mana for them.

name: hate-color-choose
description: Color hate where you choose a color to hate on.

name: heroic
description: Whenever you cast a spell targeting your permanent, something good happens.

name: dnd-monster
description: Cards named after and representing monsters from DnD.

name: hatebear
description: Creatures that are low-cost and have low-power/toughness with relevant effects that may disrupt an opponent's strategy. These are traditionally associated with white.

name: universal-type-change
description: Cards that turn every type A into type B. Might be just one player or all, just the battlefield or not.

name: regenerates-other
description: Cards with effects that regenerate other things (and possibly including themselves.)

name: bombard-self
description: Sacrifice this permanent to deal N damage. See also [fling-self](/tags/card/fling-self).

name: lockdown
description: A permanent stays tapped. Named in the Color Pie 2017 article.

name: hate-high-pt
description: Cards that specifically hate on cards with high power or toughness, typically at least 3-4.

name: fog
description: Effects that can prevent all or most of the damage from an entire combat, similar to the card Fog.

name: undergrowth
description: Cards that care about the number of creature cards in your graveyard.

name: aesthetic-counter
description: Counters that have no rules meaning, just aesthetic.

name: aesthetic-counter
description: Counters that have no rules meaning, just aesthetic.

name: threshold
description: Cards that care about you having seven or more cards in your graveyard.

name: grants-flashback
description: Cards which let you re-cast an instant or sorcery out of a graveyard, whether for free or by paying its costs. Includes cards that don't actually grant the exact flashback effect.

name: portmanteau
description: Cards named with a portmanteau—a word that's a combination of two words.

name: swap-removal
description: Sorry I messed up your stuff. Here's a thing in exchange. (See also [humble](/tags/card/humble).)

name: tutor-card
description: Cards that tutor any cards.

name: consult-cast
description: Consult effects that let you cast the card you find.

name: flowstone
description: Abilities that grant +N/-N and/or -N/+N

name: keyword-counter
description: A collection of all the keyword counters referenced by cards.

name: humble
description: Nerf a creature's stats and abilities as a form of removal. See also [shapechange](/tags/card/shapechange).

name: token-versions-of-cards
description: Some cards create tokens identical to existing cards (except for CMC). See: [cards creating these tokens](/tags/card/creates-token-of-a-card),  [printed tokens](/tags/card/token-version-of-a-card), and [the cards recreated in token form](/tags/card/has-identical-token).

name: threaten
description: Gain control of a permanent until end of turn. For continuous theft see [theft-creature](/tags/card/theft-creature).

name: aikido
description: Effects that turn your opponent's strength against them.

name: aikido
description: Effects that turn your opponent's strength against them.

name: animate-land
description: Cards that can turn other noncreature lands into creatures.

name: animate-land
description: Cards that can turn other noncreature lands into creatures.

name: titan-trigger
description: An ability that triggers on both entering the battlefield and attacking, similar to the Titan cycle from M11

name: charm
description: Modal spells where you pick one option out of three

name: tutor-cmc
description: Cards that tutor cards with a certain converted mana cost.

name: extra-land
description: Effects that allow you to put additional lands from your hand onto the battlefield outside of your normal once-per-turn land play.

name: morbid
description: Cards that care if a creature died this turn.

name: copy-self
description: Cards that make a token topy of themselves

name: one-sided-fight
description: A creature deals damage equal to its power to another. Like Fight, but without the chance to fight back. See also [fling](/tags/card/fling) which involves sacrificing the creature.

name: jump
description: A creature gains flying until end of turn.

name: mill-exile
description: Exile cards from the top of a library.

name: poisonous
description: Makes, or is, a creature that poisons a player when it hits them.

name: trigger-from-graveyard
description: Abilities that trigger from inside the graveyard.

name: thoughtseize
description: Opponent reveals their hand, and you choose a card for them to discard.

name: reanimate-cast
description: Cast a card from your graveyard.

name: counterspell-soft
description: A "soft counterspell" gives the other player a chance to buy off the counter, such as with a mana payment. See also [counterspell-hard](/tags/card/counterspell-hard)

name: virtual-legendary
description: This card represents a one-of-a-kind creature or object, and could conceivably have been legendary. Usually cards are in this category because they were printed before legendary existed or have a mechanical need to not be legendary.

name: tutored-by-name
description: These cards are tutored by another specifically by their name.

name: energy-generator
description: Cards that in some way give you energy counters.

name: unique-counter
description: These cards use a type of counter no other card does.

name: mulch
description: An effect that filters cards at the top of the library, putting remainders into the graveyard.

name: cycle-mono-land
description: Monocolor land cycles.

name: mix-and-match
description: Two or more non-evergreen mechanics blended together on the same card.

name: rhyming-name
description: Cards whose names contain a rhyme, or come very close to it.

name: sneak
description: Put a permanent from your hand onto the battlefield. (With or without a requirement to sacrifice it later.)

name: graveyard-fuel-creature
description: Exiles creatures from the graveyard for value

name: freeze
description: A permanent doesn't untap during its next N untap steps.

name: punisher
description: Effects that give you a choice of two damnations.

name: shade-pump
description: Effects that give an arbitrary amount of +1/+1 until end of turn. See also [firebreathing] in red and [armoring] in white.

name: sweeper-one-sided
description: Sweepers that are, or have high potential to be, one-sided.

name: curiosity
description: Draw cards when dealing damage to an opponent

name: quick-equip
description: Non-Equip abilities that attach equipment.

name: shapechange
description: Set creatures' power/toughness, not necessarily a nerf. See also [humble](/tags/card/humble).

name: egg
description: Artifacts that have to be sacrificed to do something.

name: regenerates-self
description: Cards with effects that regenerate themselves.

name: toughness-matters
description: Other than in, you know, the usual way.

name: mana-filter
description: Convert mana to other colors.

name: bombard
description: Sacrifice something to deal N damage. See also [fling](/tags/card/fling).

name: tuck
description: Effects that put a spell or permanent into its owner's library.

name: poison-mechanics
description: Cards and effects that interact with poison counters by name.

name: potentially-black-border
description: Silver border cards that could've been given a black border instead if they were printed today.

name: consult
description: Dig through your library until you find a card meeting some criteria.

name: deprecated-mechanics
description: Mechanics that have been deprecated by newer developments.

name: restock
description: Effects that return cards from the graveyard to the library. (Named in Maro's color pie 2017 article.)

name: rhystic
description: Effects that opponents can buy off if they pay mana.

name: dnd-character
description: Cards that represent Dungeons and Dragons characters: name, rules text, etc. See also the [dungeons and dragons](/tags/artwork/dungeons-and-dragons) art tag.

name: multiplayer
description: Cards that interact with all of the players in the game. They might scale with the number of players or affect the turn order for example.

name: tutor-creature
description: Cards that tutor creature cards.

name: surveil
description: Cards that let you look at the top # cards of your library and put some into the graveyard.

name: impulsive-draw
description: Cards which let you cast a card this turn off the top of a library. Use it or lose it. Typically a red card advantage mechanic. For the effect seen on the [card Impulse](/card/vis/34), see the [tag impulse](/tags/card/impulse).

name: landfall
description: Cards which reward you for playing lands.

name: firebreathing
description: Give a creature +X/+0 until end of turn via an activated ability.

name: reflexive-trigger
description: An ability that triggers based on actions taken earlier during a spell or ability's resolution.

name: dice-roll
description: Cards that involve rolling dice.

name: rummage
description: Discard a card, then draw a card. Mainly red. See also [loot](/tags/card/loot), the blue version, which draws then discards.

name: refund
description: Immediately get mana or untapped lands back.

name: name-matters
description: Effects that care about card names: different names, same name, specific name, etc.

name: bear-with-set-s-mechanic
description: A 2/2 for 2 with one of the set's iconic mechanics

name: pinger

name: indefinite-effect
description: Effects that last forever, sometimes tracked, sometimes untracked.

name: activate-from-graveyard

name: activate-from-graveyard
description: Abilities that can be activated from inside a graveyard.

name: rescue

description: Cards that make other spells cost less. (Does not apply to effects that reduce a spell's own cost, like delve.)

name: animate-self

name: animate-self
description: Noncreatures that can become creatures.

name: offcolor-ability
description: Abilities with a mana cost outside the card's colors.

name: anthem

description: Effects that give a creature +N/+N. This value should be significant, at least 3.

name: tutor-land-basic
description: Cards that tutor basic land cards.

name: loot
description: Draw a card, then discard a card. Mainly blue. See also [rummage](/tags/card/rummage), the red version, which discards then draws.

name: drain-life
description: Hurt your opponent and gain life to match.

name: reanimate-self
description: Cards that reanimate themselves.

name: mana-rock
description: Noncreature artifacts that net increase your mana.

name: un-set-mechanics
description: Card tags showing mechanics that (at least nowadays) only show up in un-sets.

name: un-design
description: Features characteristic of and unique to the world of un-sets.

name: mana-dork
description: Low-cost creatures which can repeatedly generate mana

name: adds-multiple-mana
description: Cards that add more than one mana at a time.

name: adds-multiple-mana
description: Cards that add more than one mana at a time.

name: dilemma
description: Effects that give you two equally bad choices.

name: martyr
description: Creatures that sacrifice themselves for benefit.

name: tapland
description: Non-basic lands which come into play tapped

name: graveyard-fuel
description: Cards that require exiling other cards in graveyard as an additional cost for abilities and effects.

name: impulse
description: Look at the top N cards and put 1+ of them into your hand. Not to be confused with Red's pseudo-card-draw effect, [impulsive draw](/tags/card/impulsive-draw).

name: creaturefall
description: Also known as Alliance in New Capenna.

name: tutor-to-battlefield
description: Cards that tutor something out of the library and straight onto the battlefield.

name: cards-in-graveyard-matter
description: Mechanics that care about the cards in one or more graveyards.

name: red-effect
description: Effects which are iconically red.

name: bounce
description: Returning a permanent from the battlefield to its owner's hand

name: dnd
description: Cards made to reference mechanical parts of the Dungeons and Dragons TRPG.

name: tutor-to-hand
description: Cards that tutor cards to the player's hand.

name: tutor-land
description: Cards that tutor land cards.

name: animate

name: animate
description: Effects that turn things into creatures.

name: tap-fuel-creature
description: Tap a creature to pay for/activate an effect

name: counterspell
description: Spells that counter stuff. See child tags for variants on the behaviour; notably [counterspell-soft](/tags/card/counterspell-soft) which gives the opponent a buyout cost.

name: power-boost-to-all
description: Cards that provide power to all creatures you control.

name: cantrip

name: discard
description: Gets cards out of your opponent's hand

name: protects-creature
description: Effects that can protect a creature, e.g. with protection,  hexproof, indestructible, etc.

name: cycle-land
description: All the land cycles. See in particular: [monocolor land cycles](/tags/card/cycle-mono-land), [dual land cycles](/tags/card/cycle-dual-land), and [triland cycles](/tags/card/cycle-triland).

name: modal
description: Spells which give you your choice from two or more distinct functions.

name: life-payment
description: Cards that cost life to use; not necessarily with the "pay" keyword.

name: hate-color
description: Color hate for one or more colors. See also [hate-colorless](/tags/card/hate-colorless).

name: theft
description: Effects that let you steal cards and resources from your opponent.

name: symmetrical
description: Cards that effect the whole battlefield/all players in symmetrical, equal manner.

name: unique-token
description: This token is created by only one card.

name: control-changing-effects
description: Effects that change control of cards, permanents, and spells.

name: copy
description: Effects that copy things

name: regrowth
description: Effects that return cards from your graveyard to your hand.

name: mana-producer
description: non-land cards which generate mana

name: burn-any
description: Cards that burn any target: players, creatures, or planeswalkers.

name: blue-effect
description: Effects which are iconically blue.

name: saboteur
description: Effects that trigger when you deal combat damage to an opponent.

name: mana-sink
description: Cards with repeatable abilities to put mana into.

name: tutor-to
description: Tutor to specific zones.

name: mill
description: A keyword action used in Magic to describe the action of a player taking cards from the top of their library and putting them into their graveyard.

name: reanimate
description: Return permanent cards from the graveyard to the battlefield.

name: virtual-french-vanilla
description: Creatures and vehicles that are french vanilla (having only keyword abilities) after entering the battlefield. They may have "enters the battlefield" or "on cast" trigger.

name: single-english-word-name
description: Cards named with a single word in English. This may be a compound word.

name: repeatable-token-generator
description: Repeatable ways to create creature tokens

name: gives-pp-counters
description: Cards that give +1/+1 counters

name: french-vanilla
description: These creatures and vehicles have only keyword abilities.

name: virtual-vanilla
description: These creatures are effectively just vanilla after entering the battlefield. They may have an enters-the-battlefield or on-cast trigger.

name: death-trigger
description: Card abilities that trigger from permanents of given type being sacrificed or destroyed (and being sent to graveyard.)

name: namesake-spell
description: Spells (or, mostly spells) with names that identify them with a specific named character.

name: noncreature-tribal
description: Cards that care about creature types, but not necessarily on a creature card—so they're compatible with the Kindred cards from Lorwyn, for example.

name: leaves-battlefield-trigger
description: Cards that trigger on something leaving the battlefield.

name: unique-type-line
description: No other card has this same type line.

name: recursion
description: Get stuff back from your graveyard to use it again. See: reanimate (to battlefield), regrowth (to hand), and restock (to library).

name: alliteration
description: Cards that alliterate, either properly or per Treacherous Trapezist.

name: alliteration
description: Cards that alliterate, either properly or per Treacherous Trapezist.

name: flavors-of-vanilla
description: Magic has various flavors of "vanilla", referencing cards with no abilities or only keyword abilities. For vanilla creatures (those with no abilities) see [is:vanilla](https://scryfall.com/search?q=is%3Avanilla) in Scryfall search.

name: evasion
description: Creatures that are harder to block through keywords (Flying, Menace) or other means.

name: removal
description: Spot or limited removal. See also [sweeper] for removal effects that remove everything.

name: card-advantage
description: Things that give you access to more cards.  (The technical meaning of card advantage can be much broader than this, but this is what we're using here.)

name: cycle
description: All the cycles from Magic history.

name: card-names
description: A collection of tags identifying properties and naming schemes in cards.
